USTDA Representative in India Mehnaz Ansari described the coming together of academic institutions as a matter of big pride. Among the three cities in the Smart City Challenge, Visakhapatnam turned out to be outstanding leader. The U.S. was a natural partner for the city and the USTDA would provide technological support in various ways and in master advisory plan. The U.S. industry was excited about Visakhapatnam, she said, adding that the MoU would bring convergence beyond business and government.